==Engish==
===Etymology===
Afrikaans: ''bak'': to bake or roast + ''gat'': bum.

===Adjective===
'''bakgat'''
#{{slang}} (corse). Great. good. fine.
#"Your car was [[pinking]] and I fixed it." "'''Bakgat'''."

====Usage note====
It is usually a positive response to a statement made by somebody else.
